Argentina, Provinces Study Higher Mining Taxes, Cronista Says

-- B y   L a u r a   P r i c e
-- 
2011-10-20T11:49:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/argentina-provinces-study-higher-mining-taxes-cronista-says.html
Argentine mineral-producing
provinces and some federal government officials are studying
higher taxes for mining companies, El Cronista said, citing
unidentified government workers and company executives.  A change in tax collection could be introduced early next
year and may involve changes in mining royalties, the Buenos
Aires-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Laura Price in  Buenos Aires  at 
 lprice3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at 
 dcrofts@bloomberg.net  